The paper also introduces variants of LCS based on shared substrings of length exactly or at least k. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the runtime complexity of the algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions empirical validation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions the use of basic data structures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DB (Databases).
